WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:12.160 --> 00:00:14.160
Brain magic. What's brain magic all about?

00:00:14.184 --> 00:00:16.351
Brain magic to me indicates
that area of magic

00:00:16.375 --> 00:00:18.852
dealing with psychological
and mind-reading effects.

00:00:19.667 --> 00:00:22.523
So unlike traditional magic,
it uses the power of words,

00:00:22.547 --> 00:00:25.143
linguistic deception,
non-verbal communication

00:00:25.167 --> 00:00:29.167
and various other techniques
to create the illusion of a sixth sense.

00:00:30.136 --> 00:00:32.112
I'm going to show you all how easy it is

00:00:32.136 --> 00:00:34.462
to manipulate the human mind
once you know how.

00:00:34.486 --> 00:00:37.591
I want everybody downstairs also
to join in with me and everybody.

00:00:37.615 --> 00:00:40.908
I want everybody to put out your hands
like this for me, first of all.

00:00:40.932 --> 00:00:42.534
OK, clap them together, once.

00:00:42.558 --> 00:00:44.136
OK, reverse your hands.

00:00:44.160 --> 00:00:46.136
Now, follow my actions exactly.

00:00:46.160 --> 00:00:49.208
Now about half the audience has
their left hand up. Why is that?

00:00:49.232 --> 00:00:51.859
OK, swap them around,
put your right hand up.

00:00:51.883 --> 00:00:54.456
Cross your hands over,
so your right hand goes over,

00:00:54.480 --> 00:00:56.457
interlace your fingers like this,

00:00:56.481 --> 00:00:59.347
then make sure your right thumb
is outside your left thumb --

00:00:59.371 --> 00:01:00.520
that's very important.

00:01:00.544 --> 00:01:02.830
Yours is the other way around,
so swap it around.

00:01:02.854 --> 00:01:05.370
Excellent, OK. Extend
your fingers like this for me.

00:01:05.891 --> 00:01:07.614
All right. Tap them together once.

00:01:08.384 --> 00:01:11.902
OK, now, if you did not allow me
to deceive your minds,

00:01:11.926 --> 00:01:13.582
you would all be able to do this.

00:01:15.900 --> 00:01:17.742
(Laughter)

00:01:19.376 --> 00:01:20.955
(Laughter ends)

00:01:20.979 --> 00:01:22.486
Now you can see how easy it is

00:01:22.510 --> 00:01:25.136
for me to manipulate the human mind,
once you know how.

00:01:25.160 --> 00:01:27.843
(Laughter)

00:01:27.867 --> 00:01:30.105
Now, I remember when I was about 15,

00:01:30.129 --> 00:01:31.699
(Laughter)

00:01:31.723 --> 00:01:33.642
I read a copy of Life magazine,

00:01:33.666 --> 00:01:38.505
which detailed a story
about a 75-year-old blind Russian woman

00:01:38.600 --> 00:01:40.252
who could sense printed letters --

00:01:40.276 --> 00:01:42.148
there's still people trying to do it --

00:01:42.172 --> 00:01:43.299
(Laughter)

00:01:43.323 --> 00:01:46.704
-- who could sense printed letters
and even sense colors, just by touch.

00:01:46.728 --> 00:01:48.136
And she was completely blind.

00:01:48.160 --> 00:01:50.399
She could also read
the serial numbers on bills

00:01:50.423 --> 00:01:52.900
when they were placed,
face down, on a hard surface.

00:01:52.924 --> 00:01:56.136
Now, I was fascinated,
but at the same time, skeptical.

00:01:56.160 --> 00:01:58.399
How could somebody read
using their fingertips?

00:01:59.302 --> 00:02:03.136
You know, if you actually think about it,
if somebody is totally blind --

00:02:03.160 --> 00:02:05.802
a guy yesterday did a demonstration
in one of the rooms,

00:02:05.826 --> 00:02:09.094
where people had to close their eyes
and they could just hear things.

00:02:09.118 --> 00:02:12.032
And it's just a really weird thing
to try and figure out.

00:02:12.056 --> 00:02:14.305
How could somebody read
using their fingertips?

00:02:14.329 --> 00:02:18.044
Now earlier on, as part of a TV show
that I have coming up on MTV,

00:02:18.068 --> 00:02:20.136
I attempted to give
a similar demonstration

00:02:20.160 --> 00:02:23.024
of what is now known as second sight.

00:02:23.048 --> 00:02:24.136
So, let's take a look.

00:02:24.160 --> 00:02:26.136
(Video) Man: There we go.

00:02:26.160 --> 00:02:28.136
I'm going to guide you into the car.

00:02:28.160 --> 00:02:29.636
Kathryn Thomas: (Laughter)

00:02:29.660 --> 00:02:31.136
Man: You're OK, keep on going.

00:02:31.160 --> 00:02:32.234
KT: How are you?

00:02:32.258 --> 00:02:34.107
Keith Barry: Kathryn, it's Keith here.

00:02:34.131 --> 00:02:37.136
I'm going to take you
to a secret location, OK?

00:02:37.160 --> 00:02:40.124
Kathryn, there was no way
you could see through that blindfold.

00:02:40.148 --> 00:02:42.936
KT: OK, but don't say my name like that.
KB: But you're OK?

00:02:42.960 --> 00:02:44.036
KT: Yes.

00:02:44.060 --> 00:02:46.136
KB: No way to see through it?
KT: No.

00:02:46.160 --> 00:02:47.435
KB: I'll take it off.

00:02:47.459 --> 00:02:49.136
Do you want to take the rest off?

00:02:49.160 --> 00:02:51.436
Take it off, you're OK.
We'll stop for a second.

00:02:51.460 --> 00:02:53.508
KT: I'm so afraid
of what I'm going to see.

00:02:53.532 --> 00:02:56.208
KB: You're fine, take it off.
You're OK. You're safe.

00:02:56.232 --> 00:02:58.136
Have you ever heard of second sight?

00:02:58.160 --> 00:02:59.196
KT: No.

00:02:59.220 --> 00:03:01.592
KB: Second sight is whereby
a mind-control expert

00:03:01.616 --> 00:03:04.136
can see through somebody else's eyes.

00:03:04.160 --> 00:03:06.160
And I'm going to try that right now.

00:03:11.160 --> 00:03:13.160
KT: God.

00:03:19.136 --> 00:03:20.136
KB: Are you ready?

00:03:21.695 --> 00:03:24.136
Where is it? There's no way --

00:03:24.160 --> 00:03:26.160
KT: (Beep)

00:03:29.382 --> 00:03:30.910
KT: Oh, my God!

00:03:30.934 --> 00:03:32.136
KB: Don't say anything,

00:03:32.160 --> 00:03:34.732
I'm trying to see through your eyes.
I can't see.

00:03:34.756 --> 00:03:36.423
KT: There's a wall, there's a wall.

00:03:36.447 --> 00:03:38.423
KB: Look at the road, look at the road.

00:03:38.447 --> 00:03:40.136
KT: OK, OK, OK. Oh, my God!

00:03:40.160 --> 00:03:42.136
KB: Now, anything coming at all?
KT: No.

00:03:42.160 --> 00:03:43.199
KB: Sure there's not?

00:03:43.223 --> 00:03:45.436
KT: No, no, I'm just still
looking at the road.

00:03:45.460 --> 00:03:47.336
I'm looking at the road, all the time.

00:03:47.359 --> 00:03:49.135
I'm not taking my eyes off the road.

00:03:49.160 --> 00:03:50.160
(Beep)

00:03:54.160 --> 00:03:55.160
(Beep)

00:03:59.153 --> 00:04:00.160
(Beep)

00:04:01.136 --> 00:04:02.136
KT: Oh, my God!

00:04:02.160 --> 00:04:04.161
KB: Where are we? Where are we?

00:04:04.185 --> 00:04:06.090
We're going uphill, are we going uphill?

00:04:07.160 --> 00:04:09.136
KT: Look at the road -- (Beep)

00:04:09.160 --> 00:04:11.136
Still got that goddamn blindfold on.

00:04:11.160 --> 00:04:12.239
KB: What?

00:04:12.263 --> 00:04:13.905
KT: How are you doing this?

00:04:13.929 --> 00:04:15.739
KB: Just don't break my concentration.

00:04:19.160 --> 00:04:21.516
We're OK, though?
KT: Yes.

00:04:27.160 --> 00:04:29.136
That's so weird.

00:04:29.160 --> 00:04:32.160
We're nearly there. Oh, my God!

00:04:34.710 --> 00:04:36.897
Oh, my God!

00:04:38.215 --> 00:04:39.838
KB: And I've stopped.

00:04:40.826 --> 00:04:42.490
KT: That is weird.

00:04:47.160 --> 00:04:50.137
You're like a freak-ass of nature.

00:04:50.161 --> 00:04:53.136
That was the most scary thing
I've ever done in my life!

00:04:53.160 --> 00:04:54.208
(Applause)

00:04:54.232 --> 00:04:56.136
KB: Thank you.

00:04:56.160 --> 00:04:59.136
By the way, two days ago,
we were going to film this

00:04:59.160 --> 00:05:02.136
down there, at the race course,
and we got a guy into a car,

00:05:02.160 --> 00:05:04.136
and we got a camera man in the back,

00:05:04.160 --> 00:05:05.697
but halfway through the drive,

00:05:05.721 --> 00:05:08.167
he told me he had,
I think it was a nine-millimeter,

00:05:08.191 --> 00:05:09.360
stuck to his leg.

00:05:09.384 --> 00:05:11.470
So, I stopped pretty quick,
and that was it.

00:05:11.494 --> 00:05:14.763
So, do you believe it's possible
to see through somebody else's eyes?

00:05:14.787 --> 00:05:15.866
That's the question.

00:05:15.890 --> 00:05:18.395
Now, most people here
would automatically say no.

00:05:18.419 --> 00:05:20.563
OK, but I want you to realize some facts.

00:05:20.587 --> 00:05:22.808
I couldn't see through the blindfold.

00:05:22.832 --> 00:05:25.642
The car was not gimmicked
or tricked in any way.

00:05:25.666 --> 00:05:28.604
The girl, I'd never met before, all right.

00:05:28.628 --> 00:05:31.108
So, I want you to just think
about it for a moment.

00:05:31.132 --> 00:05:32.786
A lot of people try to come up

00:05:32.810 --> 00:05:35.477
with a logical solution
to what just happened, all right.

00:05:35.501 --> 00:05:38.879
But because your brains are not
trained in the art of deception,

00:05:38.903 --> 00:05:40.344
the solutions you come up with

00:05:40.368 --> 00:05:42.724
will, 99 percent of the time,
be way off the mark.

00:05:43.502 --> 00:05:46.136
This is because magic
is all about directing attention.

00:05:46.160 --> 00:05:49.077
If, for instance, I didn't want
you to look at my right hand,

00:05:49.101 --> 00:05:50.336
then I don't look at it.

00:05:50.360 --> 00:05:53.131
But if I wanted you
to look at my right hand,

00:05:53.155 --> 00:05:54.377
then I look at it, too.

00:05:54.401 --> 00:05:56.520
You see, it's very simple,
once you know how,

00:05:56.544 --> 00:05:58.247
but very complicated in other ways.

00:05:58.271 --> 00:06:00.788
I'm going to give you
some demonstrations right now.

00:06:00.812 --> 00:06:03.670
I need two people to help me out
real quick. Can you come up?

00:06:03.694 --> 00:06:07.730
And let's see, down at the end, here,
can you also come up, real quick?

00:06:07.754 --> 00:06:09.136
Do you mind? Yes, at the end.

00:06:09.160 --> 00:06:11.541
OK, give them a round of applause
as they come up.

00:06:11.565 --> 00:06:13.541
You might want to use the stairs, there.

00:06:13.565 --> 00:06:16.137
(Applause)

00:06:16.161 --> 00:06:18.462
It's very important
for everybody here to realize

00:06:18.486 --> 00:06:20.236
I haven't set anything up with you.

00:06:20.260 --> 00:06:22.134
You don't know what will happen, right?

00:06:22.158 --> 00:06:24.635
Would you mind just standing
over here for a moment?

00:06:24.659 --> 00:06:26.053
Your name is?
Nicole: Nicole.

00:06:26.077 --> 00:06:27.084
KB: Nicole, and?

00:06:27.108 --> 00:06:28.117
(Telephone ringing)

00:06:28.141 --> 00:06:32.073
KB: Actually, here's the thing,
answer it, answer it, answer it.

00:06:32.097 --> 00:06:33.136
(Laughter)

00:06:33.160 --> 00:06:35.136
Is it a girl?
Man: They've already gone.

00:06:35.160 --> 00:06:36.510
KB: OK, swap over positions.

00:06:36.534 --> 00:06:39.136
Can you stand over here?
This will make it easier.

00:06:39.160 --> 00:06:41.736
Pity, I would have told them
