00:11:57.792 --> 00:12:00.120
and it landed on the ground,
and it didn't break?

00:12:00.144 --> 00:12:02.468
Now, see, that's because
Coke bottles are solid.

00:12:03.006 --> 00:12:06.293
It's nearly impossible
to break a Coke bottle.

00:12:06.317 --> 00:12:07.714
Do you want to try it?

00:12:09.429 --> 00:12:11.835
Good job. She's not taking any chances.

00:12:11.859 --> 00:12:13.136
(Laughter)

00:12:13.160 --> 00:12:15.541
You see, psychokinesis
is the paranormal influence

00:12:15.565 --> 00:12:18.048
of the mind on physical
events and processes.

00:12:18.542 --> 00:12:20.136
For some magicians or mentalists,

00:12:20.160 --> 00:12:24.136
sometimes the spoon will bend
or melt, sometimes it will not.

00:12:24.160 --> 00:12:27.644
Sometimes the object will slide
across the table, sometimes it will not.

00:12:27.668 --> 00:12:29.940
It depends on how much
energy you have that day,

00:12:29.964 --> 00:12:31.028
so on and so forth.

00:12:31.052 --> 00:12:33.910
We're going to try an experiment
in psychokinesis, right now.

00:12:33.934 --> 00:12:36.063
Come right over here, next to me.
Excellent.

00:12:36.087 --> 00:12:37.872
Now, have a look at the Coke bottle.

00:12:37.896 --> 00:12:41.468
Make sure it is solid, there's only
one hole, and it's a normal Coke bottle.

00:12:41.492 --> 00:12:44.493
And you can whack it against the table,
if you want; be careful.

00:12:44.517 --> 00:12:46.517
Even though it's solid, I'm standing away.

00:12:46.541 --> 00:12:49.891
I want you to pinch right here
with two fingers and your thumb.

00:12:49.915 --> 00:12:52.469
Excellent.
Now, I've got a shard of glass here, OK.

00:12:52.493 --> 00:12:54.446
I want you to examine the shard of glass.

00:12:54.470 --> 00:12:57.045
Careful, it's sharp.
Just hold on to it for a moment.

00:12:57.069 --> 00:12:58.236
Now, hold it out here.

00:12:58.261 --> 00:13:02.161
I want you to imagine, right now,
a broken relationship from many years ago.

00:13:02.707 --> 00:13:05.788
I want you to imagine
all the negative energy

00:13:05.812 --> 00:13:07.964
from that broken
relationship, from that guy,

00:13:07.988 --> 00:13:10.492
being imparted into the broken
piece of glass,

00:13:10.516 --> 00:13:12.136
which will represent him, OK.

00:13:12.160 --> 00:13:14.208
But I want you to take this
very seriously.

00:13:14.232 --> 00:13:16.518
Stare at the glass,
ignore everybody right here.

00:13:16.542 --> 00:13:19.665
In a moment, you'll feel
a certain sensation, OK,

00:13:19.689 --> 00:13:21.505
and when you feel that sensation,

00:13:21.529 --> 00:13:24.136
I want you to drop the piece
of glass into the bottle.

00:13:24.160 --> 00:13:29.057
Think of that guy, that ba -- that guy.

00:13:29.081 --> 00:13:30.136
(Laughter)

00:13:30.160 --> 00:13:31.573
I'm trying to be good here.

00:13:31.597 --> 00:13:33.407
OK, and when you feel the sensation --

00:13:33.431 --> 00:13:35.690
it might take a while --
drop it into the glass.

00:13:47.969 --> 00:13:48.969
OK, drop it in.

00:13:49.501 --> 00:13:52.136
Now, imagine all that negative
energy in there.

00:13:52.160 --> 00:13:54.793
Imagine his name
and imagine him inside the glass.

00:13:54.817 --> 00:13:57.061
And I want you to release
that negative energy

00:13:57.085 --> 00:13:58.609
by shaking it from side to side.

00:13:59.726 --> 00:14:00.727
(Burst)

00:14:00.751 --> 00:14:03.136
(Laughter)

00:14:03.160 --> 00:14:05.692
That was a lot of negative energy,
built up in there.

00:14:05.716 --> 00:14:07.778
(Laughter)

00:14:07.802 --> 00:14:11.136
(Applause)

00:14:11.160 --> 00:14:14.161
I also want you to look at me
and think of his name.

00:14:14.185 --> 00:14:18.160
OK, think of how many letters
in the title of his name.

00:14:18.184 --> 00:14:19.866
There's five letters in the title.

00:14:19.890 --> 00:14:22.137
You didn't react to that,
so it's four letters.

00:14:22.161 --> 00:14:24.136
Think of one of the letters in the title.

00:14:24.160 --> 00:14:26.136
There's a K in his name, there is a K.

00:14:26.160 --> 00:14:28.536
I knew that because my name
starts with a K also,

00:14:28.560 --> 00:14:31.397
but his name doesn't start
with a K, it starts with an M.

00:14:31.421 --> 00:14:33.843
Tell Mike I said hello,
the next time you see him.

00:14:33.867 --> 00:14:35.536
Was that his name?
Nicole: Mm-hmm.

00:14:35.560 --> 00:14:37.337
KB: OK, give her a round of applause.

00:14:37.361 --> 00:14:42.969
(Applause)

00:14:42.993 --> 00:14:44.136
Thank you.

00:14:44.160 --> 00:14:46.118
(Applause)

00:14:49.329 --> 00:14:50.628
(Applause ends)

00:14:50.652 --> 00:14:53.136
I've got one more thing
to share with you right now.

00:14:53.160 --> 00:14:55.541
Actually, Chris, I was going
to pick you for this,

00:14:55.565 --> 00:14:57.804
but instead of picking you,
can you hop up here

00:14:57.828 --> 00:15:00.136
and pick a victim
for this next experiment?

00:15:00.160 --> 00:15:02.732
And it should be a male victim,
that's the only thing.

00:15:02.756 --> 00:15:04.136
Chris Anderson: Oh, OK.

00:15:04.160 --> 00:15:05.546
KB: I was going to use you,

00:15:05.570 --> 00:15:08.136
but I decided I might want
to come back another year.

00:15:08.160 --> 00:15:09.175
(Laughter)

00:15:09.199 --> 00:15:11.311
CA: Well, to reward him
for saying "eureka,"

00:15:11.335 --> 00:15:14.903
and for selecting Michael Mercil to come
and talk to us -- Steve Jurvetson.

00:15:14.927 --> 00:15:16.673
KB: OK, Steve, come on up here.

00:15:16.697 --> 00:15:17.769
(Applause)

00:15:17.793 --> 00:15:18.834
CA: You knew!

00:15:18.858 --> 00:15:23.160
KB: OK, Steve, I want you to take
a seat, right behind here. Excellent.

00:15:24.849 --> 00:15:27.136
Now, Steve -- oh, you
can check underneath.

00:15:28.960 --> 00:15:31.523
Go ahead, I've no fancy
assistants underneath there.

00:15:31.547 --> 00:15:34.062
They insist that because I was a magician,

00:15:34.086 --> 00:15:35.626
put a nice, black tablecloth on.

00:15:35.650 --> 00:15:37.063
There you are, OK.

00:15:37.087 --> 00:15:38.136
(Laughter)

00:15:38.160 --> 00:15:40.136
I've got four wooden plinths here, Steve.

00:15:40.160 --> 00:15:43.136
One, two, three and four.

00:15:43.160 --> 00:15:45.399
Now, they're all the exact
same except this one

00:15:45.423 --> 00:15:48.138
obviously has a stainless steel
spike sticking out of it.

00:15:48.162 --> 00:15:50.627
I want you to examine it,
and make sure it's solid.

00:15:53.255 --> 00:15:54.262
Happy?

00:15:54.286 --> 00:15:56.240
Steve Jurvetson: Mmm, yes.

00:15:56.264 --> 00:15:59.771
KB: OK. Now, Steve, I'm going
to stand in front of the table,

00:15:59.795 --> 00:16:01.567
When I stand in front of the table,

00:16:01.591 --> 00:16:03.706
I want you to put the cups on the plinths,

00:16:03.730 --> 00:16:05.969
in any order you want,
and then mix them all up,

00:16:05.993 --> 00:16:08.764
so nobody has any idea where
the spike is, all right?

00:16:08.788 --> 00:16:10.136
SJ: No one in the audience?

00:16:10.160 --> 00:16:12.136
KB: Yes, and just to help you out,

00:16:12.160 --> 00:16:15.146
I'll block them from view,
so nobody can see what you're doing.

00:16:15.170 --> 00:16:17.742
I'll also look away. So, go
ahead and mix them up, now.

00:16:17.766 --> 00:16:19.442
OK, and tell me when you're done.

00:16:22.093 --> 00:16:24.076
(Laughter)

00:16:24.870 --> 00:16:27.330
(Laughter)

00:16:28.732 --> 00:16:30.732
KB: You done?
SJ: Almost.

00:16:30.756 --> 00:16:33.693
KB: Almost, oh. OK, you're making
sure that's well hidden.

00:16:34.693 --> 00:16:39.136
Oh, we've got one here,
we've got one here.

00:16:39.160 --> 00:16:42.136
(Applause)

00:16:42.160 --> 00:16:44.160
So, all right, we'll leave them like that.

00:16:44.184 --> 00:16:46.136
(Laughter)

00:16:46.160 --> 00:16:48.161
I'm going to have the last laugh, though.

00:16:48.185 --> 00:16:50.136
(Laughter)

00:16:50.160 --> 00:16:55.136
Now, Steve, you know where the spike is,
but nobody else, does? Correct?

00:16:55.160 --> 00:16:58.399
But I don't want you to know either,
so swivel around on your chair.

00:16:59.375 --> 00:17:02.423
They'll keep an eye on me
to make sure I don't do anything funny.

00:17:02.447 --> 00:17:04.494
No, stay around, OK.

00:17:11.036 --> 00:17:12.718
Now, Steve, look back.

00:17:12.742 --> 00:17:16.512
Now you don't know where the spike is,
and I don't know where it is either.

00:17:16.536 --> 00:17:19.003
Now, is there any way to see
through this blindfold?

00:17:19.682 --> 00:17:20.714
SJ: Put this on?

00:17:20.738 --> 00:17:23.485
KB: No, just, is there any way
to see through it? No?

00:17:23.509 --> 00:17:26.136
SJ: No, I can't see through it.
KB: Excellent.

00:17:26.160 --> 00:17:28.024
Now, I'm going to put on the blindfold.

00:17:28.048 --> 00:17:30.481
Don't stack them up, OK.
Give them an extra mix up.

00:17:30.505 --> 00:17:33.786
Don't move the cups, I don't want
anybody to see where the spike is,

00:17:33.810 --> 00:17:36.886
but give the plinths an extra mix up,
and then line them up.

00:17:36.910 --> 00:17:39.756
I'll put the blindfold on.
Give them an extra mix up.

00:17:39.780 --> 00:17:42.353
No messing around this time.
OK, go ahead, mix them up.

00:17:42.377 --> 00:17:44.377
My hand is at risk here.

00:17:47.136 --> 00:17:48.136
(Laughter)

00:17:48.160 --> 00:17:50.136
Tell me when you're done.
SJ: Done.

00:17:50.160 --> 00:17:53.136
KB: OK, where are you?
Put out your hand. Your right hand.

00:17:53.160 --> 00:17:55.136
Tell me when I'm over a cup.

00:17:55.160 --> 00:17:57.637
SJ: You're over a cup.
KB: I'm over a cup, right now?

00:17:57.661 --> 00:17:58.721
SJ: Mm-hmm.

00:17:58.745 --> 00:18:01.136
KB: Now, Steve, do you think
it's here? Yes or no?

00:18:01.160 --> 00:18:02.445
SJ: Oh!

00:18:02.469 --> 00:18:04.136
(Laughter)

00:18:04.160 --> 00:18:06.136
KB: I told you I'd have the last laugh.

00:18:06.160 --> 00:18:11.031
(Laughter)

00:18:11.055 --> 00:18:14.530
SJ: I don't think it's there.
KB: No? Good decision.

00:18:14.554 --> 00:18:17.136
(Laughter)

00:18:17.160 --> 00:18:19.610
(Applause)

00:18:22.721 --> 00:18:24.136
(Applause ends)

00:18:24.160 --> 00:18:26.732
Now, if I go this way,
is there another cup over here?

00:18:26.756 --> 00:18:28.136
SJ: Can we do the left hand?

00:18:28.160 --> 00:18:32.136
KB: Oh, no, no, no. He asked me could
he do the left hand. Absolutely not.

00:18:32.160 --> 00:18:33.836
(Laughter)

00:18:33.860 --> 00:18:36.314
KB: If I go this way,
is there another cup?

00:18:36.338 --> 00:18:38.152
SJ: Yes.
KB: Tell me when to stop.

00:18:38.176 --> 00:18:39.294
SJ: OK.
KB: There?

00:18:39.318 --> 00:18:40.358
SJ: Yes, there's one.

00:18:40.382 --> 00:18:43.969
KB: OK. Do you think it's here, yes or no?
This is your decision, not mine.

00:18:43.993 --> 00:18:46.805
(Laughter)

00:18:47.818 --> 00:18:50.136
SJ: I'm going to say no.
KB: Good decision.

00:18:50.160 --> 00:18:52.136
(Laughter)

00:18:52.160 --> 00:18:54.136
OK, give me both hands.

00:18:54.160 --> 00:18:57.952
Now, put them on both cups.

00:18:57.976 --> 00:19:01.602
Do you think the spike
is under your left or your right hand?

00:19:01.666 --> 00:19:03.136
SJ: Neither.

00:19:03.160 --> 00:19:05.136
KB: Neither, oh, OK.

00:19:05.160 --> 00:19:06.718
But if you were to guess.

00:19:06.742 --> 00:19:09.112
(Laughter)

00:19:09.136 --> 00:19:11.536
SJ: Under my right hand.
KB: Under your right hand?

00:19:11.560 --> 00:19:14.037
Now, remember, you made
all the decisions all along.

00:19:14.061 --> 00:19:15.696
Psychologists, figure this out.

00:19:15.720 --> 00:19:16.811
(SJ gasps)

00:19:16.835 --> 00:19:18.136
Have a look.

00:19:18.160 --> 00:19:19.161
SJ: Oh!

00:19:19.185 --> 00:19:22.480
(Applause)

00:19:22.504 --> 00:19:24.504
KB: Thank you.

00:19:28.898 --> 00:19:31.136
(Applause ends)

00:19:31.160 --> 00:19:33.732
If anybody wants to see
some sleight of hand later on,

00:19:33.756 --> 00:19:35.136
I'll be outside.

00:19:35.160 --> 00:19:36.254
Thank you.

00:19:36.278 --> 00:19:37.953
(Applause)

00:19:37.977 --> 00:19:39.954
Thank you.

00:19:39.978 --> 00:19:41.136
Thank you.

